ther came and said, Swain, that's - he was R.H. Swain, I don't know if you've heard of R.H. Swain - a big brigade man. He says, Swain wants you. Well I mean I went into a collapse straight away. Went up there you know and - he talked down his nose like th
at you see this big fellow, he looked up and me and he said, good morning, your name Jackson? I said, yes sir. He said, I hear you play cricket Jackson? Yes sir. How would you like to play for my team? In fact if you don't you're finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14646436 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1524386\charrsid13577520 He said it in those words?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3278972 LJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1524386\charrsid13577520 That's right. No, no, he said that. He said, if you don't you're finished.

